           defined or whether outgoing particles represent only   9000103100008O
           sum of emitted nucleons.                               9000103100009O

               So far used only for charged particle data         9000103100011O
(M)        Uncertain if formation via isomeric trans. included    9000103100012

           is regarded by the compiler as uncertain. Explanation  9000103100014 
           is obligatory.                                         9000103100015

SUBDICT       90001236   20231015 Quantities (REACTION SF 5-8)    9000123600001 
           This dictionary should include all combinations of     9000123600002 
           codes in SF5-8 existing in the files. New combinations 9000123600003 
           should be communicated to NDS for inclusion in this    9000123600004 
           dictionary. Without entry in this dictionary the       9000123600005 
           following general modifiers may be added to the        9000123600006 
           quantities listed. These general modifiers must be     9000123600007 
           coded after any modifier included in dict.36.          9000123600008 
            RAW = raw data            AV = average                9000123600009 
            REL = relative data      SPA = spectrum average       9000123600010 
            FCT = times a factor     MXW = maxwellian average     9000123600011 
            FIS = fission spectrum av.                            9000123600012 
            FST = fast reactor neutron spectrum average           9000123600013 
            A    = times natural isotopic abundance               9000123600014 
            (A)  = unclear whether corr.for nat.isotop.abundance  9000123600015 
            BRA = bremsstrahlung spectrum average (for PhotoND)   9000123600016 
            BRS = average over part of bremsstrahlung spectrum    9000123600017 
            MSC  = unusual data type, see text for definition     9000123600018 
                   (use with code from dict.36 closest to data)   9000123600019 
            EPI = epithermal neutron spectrum average             9000123600020
